# Runtime data — files written by the loop, scheduled tasks, or the
# Layer 2 agent on the fly. NEVER commit these — they diverge between
# every push and every loop tick. If you find a new tracked file under
# data/ that the loop is appending/overwriting, follow the same fix
# pattern from chore/git-tracking-hygiene-20260502: add to this list,
# `git rm --cached <path>`, commit. The on-disk file is preserved.
#
# RUNTIME vs SNAPSHOT: data/morning_briefing.json and
# data/daily_research_*.json look runtime (overwritten daily by
# scripts/after-hours-research.bat) but are intentionally tracked —
# the user commits each day's research as a snapshot. Don't add them
# here unless you also kill the daily research-commit workflow.
